4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE NAME, VOICE, AND
5 LIKENESS OF INDIVIDUALS; PROVIDING RIGHTS IN THE USE OF A NAME, VOICE, OR LIKENESS;
6 PROVIDING PENALTIES; AND PROVIDING DEFINITIONS.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Property right in use of names, voices, and likenesses -- penalties
11 for unauthorized use. (1) Each individual must have property rights in their name, voice, and likeness.
12 Whether or not an individual commercially benefits during their lifetime, their rights:
13 (a) must be freely transferable and descendible, in whole or in part;
14 (b) may not expire on the death of the individual; and
15 (c) must be exclusive to the individual during their lifetime, subject to the transfer of rights as
16 provided in subsection (1)(a), and to the executors, heirs, transferees, or devisees for a period of 10 years after
17 the death of the individual unless:
18 (i) the name, voice, or likeness of an individual remains in use for commercial purposes by all
19 executors, heirs, transferees, or devisees; or
20 (ii) all executors, heirs, transferees, or devisees of the individual exercising the individual's
21 property rights are deceased.
22 (2) A person must be liable for damages as set forth in subsections (3) or (4) if the person, without
23 consent of the individual exercising the individual's property rights or the holder of the individual's property
24 rights:
25 (a) distributes, transmits, or otherwise makes available to the public an algorithm, software, tool, or
26 other technology, service, or device of which the primary purpose or function is to produce one or more digital
27 voice replicas or digital depictions of the particular, identified individual;
28 (b) publishes, performs, distributes, transmits, or makes available to the public a digital voice
