1 replica or digital depiction with knowledge that the digital voice replica or digital depiction is not authorized by
2 the individual or the holder of the individual's property rights; or
3 (c) materially contributes to, directs, or facilitates any of the conduct set forth in subsections (2)(a)
4 or (2)(b) with knowledge that the individual or the holder of the individual's property rights has not consented to
5 the conduct.
6 (3) A person who violates subsection (2)(a) shall be liable to the injured person for $50,000 for
7 each violation for each person or the actual damages suffered by the person, whichever is greater, plus any
8 profits from the unauthorized use of the individual's name, voice, or likeness.
9 (4) A person who violates subsection (2)(b) or (2)(c) shall be liable to the injured person for $5,000
10 for each violation for each person or the actual damages suffered by the person, whichever is greater, plus any
11 profits from the unauthorized use of the individual's name, voice, or likeness.
12 (5) (a) In establishing profits under subsection (3) or (4), the injured party must be required only to
13 present proof of the gross revenue being either directly or indirectly attributable to the unauthorized use.
14 (b) The person who violates this section must be required to prove the person's expenses are
15 deductible from this violation.
16 (c) Punitive damages and reasonable attorney fees may also be awarded to the injured party.
17 (6) A defense to an allegation of a violation of subsection (2) may not be that the unauthorized
18 user displays or otherwise communicates to the public a disclaimer stating that use is unauthorized or that the
19 individual or owner of the individual's rights did not participate in the creation, development, distribution, or
20 dissemination of the unauthorized digital voice replica or digital depiction.
21 (7) An action to enforce this section may be brought by:
22 (a) the individual whose name, voice, or likeness is at issue; or
23 (b) any other person to which the individual has assigned, bequeathed, transferred, or exclusively
24 licensed their name, voice, or likeness rights.
25 (8) To the extent the use is protected by the first amendment to the United States constitution, it
26 may not be a violation if the use is:
27 (a) by a news-gathering organization;
28 (b) in connection with a news report, public affairs report, sports broadcast, or account;
