1 (c) for the purposes of comment, criticism, scholarship, satire, or parody;
2 (d) a representation of an individual as themself in audiovisual works as defined in 17 U.S.C. 101,
3 unless the work containing the use is intended to create, and does create, the false impression that the work is
4 an authentic recording in which the individual participated;
5 (e) fleeting or negligible; or
6 (f) in an advertisement or commercial announcement for a work described in this subsection (7).
7 (9) No civil action may be maintained under the provisions of this section unless it is commenced
8 within 4 years after the party seeking to bring the claim discovered, or should have reasonably discovered, the
9 violation.
10 (10) For the purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
11 (a) "Digital depiction" means a replica, imitation, or approximation of the likeness of an individual
12 that is created or altered in whole or in part using digital technology in a way that the individual is depicted in a
13 manner in which the individual did not actually appear.
14 (b) "Digital voice replica" means an audio rendering that is created or altered in whole or in part
15 using digital technology and is fixed in a sound recording or audiovisual work that includes replications,
16 imitations, or approximations of the voice of an individual engaging in expression that the individual did not
17 actually perform.
18 (c) "Individual" means a natural person, living or dead, and includes the estate of an incompetent
19 or deceased individual.
20 (d) "Likeness" means an actual or simulated physical depiction or representation, digital depiction
21 or representation, or other form of depiction or representation of an individual, regardless of the means of
22 creation, that is readily identifiable as the individual by virtue of the individual's face, outward appearance, or
23 other distinguishing characteristic, or other information displayed in connection with the readily identifiable
24 characteristics of the individual.
25 (e) "Person" means an individual, firm, association, partnership, corporation, joint stock company,
26 syndicate, receiver, common law trust, conservator, statutory trust, or any other concern by whatever name
27 known or however organized, formed, or created, and includes not-for-profit corporations, associations,
28 educational and religious institutions, political parties, and community, civic, and other organizations.
